    <bioghist>Arthur J. Kosino, a resident of Detroit and later Monroe, Mich., served in the U.S. Army Air Force during World War II. In April 1944 he bailed out of a crippled B-17 over Germany and was held as a prisoner-of-war for the remainder of the war.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>The collection includes Kosino's reminiscence, "My Story of Army Life and Combat Experience during World War II;" a description of the experience of the pilot of Kosino's plane, Ed Michael, who was awarded the Medal of Honor, "Lt. Michael's Own Story;" and an illustrated account of life as a prisoner-of-war by Ben H. Phelper, "Kriegie Memories." Phelper was held in the same POW camp as Kosino, and Kosino has added comments to the book.</scopecontent>
